## Anti-bloat — keep it simple

- This file (GEMINI.md) = always-on judgment guidance
- Slash commands (`commands/*.toml`) = on-demand workflow shortcuts
- Hooks (`hooks/hooks.json`) = deterministic enforcement
- Skills (`skills/<name>/SKILL.md`) = on-demand deep workflow
- Bloat = Gemini ignores rules. Move infrequent guidance to skills.

## Code intelligence — manual + MCP

- Before edit symbol → read callers via Gemini's file tools or GitNexus MCP
- Before commit → `git diff` + lint + typecheck
- Before re-deciding → search project history (`git log --grep=...`) or
  MemPalace MCP if connected
- After major decision → write a brief ADR or save to MemPalace KG

If GitNexus / MemPalace MCP servers are connected via the user's Gemini MCP
config, use them. Otherwise fall back to plain `git` + `rg`.

## Session hygiene

- Restart Gemini between unrelated tasks
- `gemini --resume <id>` to pick up a previous session
- Long task spans sessions → summarize state before exiting

## Before ship — STOP

- Run `/ship` (S1-S5, T1-T6, F1-F5, evidence) — or run gates manually
- For high-risk surface (auth/billing/migrations) → `/careful` first, then
  spawn external reviewer:
  - If Codex installed: `codex exec --prompt "review this diff..."`
  - If Claude Code installed: `claude -p "review this diff for correctness"`
  - Otherwise: Lead self-reviews with adversarial mindset

Reviewer gap: Gemini's native peer-review channel is limited. Self-review
carries more weight here than on Claude Code or Codex.

## Hard stops — STOP and ask user

- 50k+ tokens no convergence → summarize + ask
- File system disagrees with claim → trust file, re-verify
- Destructive cmd (`rm -rf` / `git reset --hard` / force push) → announce + try reversible first
- User's intent unclear after 1 clarification → ask, don't guess

## Search

| Need | Tool |
|------|------|
| Plain text / filename | `rg` |
| Symbol / caller / impact | GitNexus MCP if connected, else `rg` + Read |
| External docs / pricing / news | Gemini's web/grounding tool |

## Verification (post-change evidence)

Every change → show evidence (test output / curl / log). Can't verify → state why + risk.
UI change → drive a browser tool yourself. NEVER ask user for screenshot.

## Code quality + anti-spaghetti

- Match existing style — don't refactor adjacent unbroken code
- One source of truth — search before adding new helper/schema/type
- Surgical — every changed line traces to user request
- Comments only for intent / non-obvious
- No new deps without clear win
- Same pattern in 3+ places → centralize

## Goal-driven

Vague → verifiable goal. "add validation" → write test for invalid input → make pass.
"Fix bug" → reproducing test → fix until pass. "Refactor X" → tests pass before AND after.
Multi-step → state plan as `[step] → verify: [check]` per row.

